headline: Trane Technologies Reports Strong Third Quarter Results
summary: Trane Technologies plc (NYSE:TT), a global climate innovator, today reported diluted earnings per share (EPS) from continuing operations of $3.82 for the third quarter of 2025. Adjusted continuing EPS was $3.88, up 15 percent.

headline: Trane Technologies (TT): Net Profit Margin Rises to 13.9%, Reinforcing Margin Strength Narrative
summary: Trane Technologies (TT) posted a robust 22.3% earnings growth over the past year, bringing its net profit margin to 13.9%, up from 12.5% the year before. Over the past five years, the company has averaged 21% annual earnings growth. Looking ahead, EPS is forecast to grow at 9.7% per year while revenue is projected to notch 7% annual gains. Investors will likely weigh these consistent gains against Trane’s premium valuation and moderating growth compared to the broader market throughout this...
